Node argv

<span key="787fbff26d9a475787e9afba5a8270c6"><span offset-key="787fbff26d9a475787e9afba5a8270c6:0">Node.js | process.argv Property</span></span>

<span key="cc17f892247e461d8420b22dd2207fa8"><span offset-key="cc17f892247e461d8420b22dd2207fa8:0">The </span>**process.argv property**<span offset-key="cc17f892247e461d8420b22dd2207fa8:2"> is an inbuilt application programming interface of the process module which is used to get the arguments passed to the node.js process when run in the command line.</span></span>

<span key="4573680905cd4ac2a0b6a0a78ed99ef9">**Syntax:**</span>

<span key="9b8617df65c34e80903bfbad86a0cce7"><span offset-key="9b8617df65c34e80903bfbad86a0cce7:0">process.argv</span></span>

<span key="06486a9132da4f9393cb733e02e4cce2">**Return Value:**<span offset-key="06486a9132da4f9393cb733e02e4cce2:1"> This property returns an array containing the arguments passed to the process when run it in the command line. The first element is the process execution path and the second element is the path for the js file.</span></span>

<span key="8dacb268ac5e4db8aa526425ae58dcf1"><span offset-key="8dacb268ac5e4db8aa526425ae58dcf1:0">Below examples illustrate the use of </span>**process.argv property**<span offset-key="8dacb268ac5e4db8aa526425ae58dcf1:2"> in Node.js:</span></span>

<span key="b616300295c34177a4513e42fd5af4c1">**Example 1:**</span>

<span key="15ff856f8144466ba591e43cafa3f3d0">``` const process = require(``'process'``); ```</span>

<span key="8389761615ac4db9a19ab666b768ea39">`console.log(process.argv);`</span>

<span key="6030a9afe4af49db9795232dedefe3a4">**Command to run the code:**</span>

<span key="cf274e8f6c4445cdbf65e9bfe52208b8"><span offset-key="cf274e8f6c4445cdbf65e9bfe52208b8:0">node index.js extra\_argument1 extra\_argument2 3</span></span>

<span key="5295188209e1474a89b7c1b2a2e0e03f">**Output:**</span>

<span key="93d99e8d0e2d4289bb4f18e3dd3b8edc"><span offset-key="93d99e8d0e2d4289bb4f18e3dd3b8edc:0">\[ ‘C:\\\\Program Files\\\\nodejs\\\\node.exe', ‘C:\\\\nodejs\\\\g\\\\process\\\\argv\_1.js', ‘extra\_argument1', ‘extra\_argument2', ‘3' \]</span></span>

<span key="316b4b68a9984b84a6c498ca4e6fc2c3">**Example 2:**</span>

<span key="6b1f8533719b45619505085114c905a9">``` const process = require(``'process'``); ```</span>

<span key="7856d8bf1ad548098089b58c635e345e">`var`<span offset-key="7856d8bf1ad548098089b58c635e345e:1"> </span>`args = process.argv;`</span>

<span key="ac195758ccdd44f8bede0581bdb7b4f3">``` console.log(``"number of arguments is "``+args.length); ```</span>

<span key="1f3fd139e77443fc9431710f1999bd13">`args.forEach((val, index) => {`</span>

<span key="a1b6142946f7469895f7e4d14c69d94d">`` console.log(`${index}: ${val}`); ``</span>

<span key="734597977e7648a8a618ae451152e51c">`});`</span>

<span key="a87aa775bb8e4610bebef0d43aee5369">**Command to run the code:**</span>

<span key="4f75a9527e144e279e8c2c5aa4352151"><span offset-key="4f75a9527e144e279e8c2c5aa4352151:0">node index.js extra\_argument1 extra\_argument2 3</span></span>

<span key="e49542bff56c4f90955829219fb3c454">**Output:**</span>

<span key="5d627637fda1486cabe6f3071526ca6a"><span offset-key="5d627637fda1486cabe6f3071526ca6a:0">number of arguments is 5 0: C:\\Program Files\\nodejs\\node.exe 1: C:\\nodejs\\g\\process\\argv\_2.js 2: extra\_argument1 3: extra\_argument2 4: 3</span></span>

<span key="e9c8eb053d0345918e5257d820ef9bd4">**Note:**<span offset-key="e9c8eb053d0345918e5257d820ef9bd4:1"> The above program will compile and run by using the </span>`node filename.js`<span offset-key="e9c8eb053d0345918e5257d820ef9bd4:3"> command followed by arguments.</span></span>
